name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: I’m thrilled to celebrate #womenshistorymonth2022  with the historic nomination of Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson to #SCOTUS. Now let's make sure Judge Jackson is quickly confirmed by the Senate. This is how history is made!

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: Equal Pay Day is an appalling reminder that we still have a long way to go to achieve true gender parity. Today marks how far into the new year a woman must work to make the same as a man made the previous year, and it only gets worse for women of color. We must do better.

tweet: Today is #WorldMentalHealthDay ! It is important to elevate this issue so we can support all those who struggle day in and day out. Your mental health is as real & important as your physical health, & more resources to address it must be provided by government at all levels.

tweet: 1/2  October is Cybersecurity Awareness Month and my office has seen an increase in reported data breaches in 2021. Now is the time to do a ‘cyber security clean-up’! Make sure your passwords are strong & the software on all of your devices is up to date.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: Some are outright scammers, but many are just businesses looking for a quick buck. They could be unlicensed contractors looking for jobs or price-gouging vendors of bottled water or cleaning products. It can feel overwhelming when your home & community have been damaged.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: We wanted to make a guide delivered to people in real time w/ information to stay safe from a disaster-related scam or fraud. Throughout the pandemic and heat waves, ice storms, wildfire smoke & more, dishonest individuals are always lurking...

tweet: Sept is Nat'l Disaster Preparedness Month. The OR DoJ, Dept of Consumer & Business Services, & Construction Contractors Board prepared a resource guide for working with your insurance co, hiring a contractor to help rebuild, spotting a disaster-related scam, & how to get help.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: Flavored nicotine products attract kids to dangerous, habit-forming products that jeopardize their health. Banning candy, mint, fruit & menthol flavors from tobacco products is essential to eliminating the appeal of the products to youth consumers.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: After the success of a bill I championed last session to make it illegal in Oregon to sell vaping products online, I joined a group of AGs to urge the FDA to deny all premarket tobacco product applications (PMTAs) for e-cig and oral products w/ high levels of nicotine & flavors.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: The Office of Mgmt and Budget (OMB) needs to develop a truly comprehensive measure of the damage caused by greenhouse gases. It would show the investments necessary to fulfill the Paris Agmt are economically justified, and our world will be safer & healthier bc we took action.

name: Ellen Rosenblum
tweet: If the Biden administration fails to update this key metric, it could doom our efforts to tackle the climate crisis. The calculation does not currently include the health effects of wildfires like the ones Oregon is experiencing.
